<!-- IMMERSIVE CHAT — the open conversation wears the SAME wallpaper as home. The home wallpaper is already
     painted ONCE, edge-to-edge, by the fixed .holo-backdrop canvas (the shared holo.theme.v1 wallpaper, run
     through the OS super-res lens). The thread pane used to sit on an opaque #0b141a that covered it; here we
     make the pane's surfaces translucent so that ONE backdrop shows straight through — so the chat is literally
     the same wallpaper as home, live-synced with it, zero extra fetch. Gated on .holo-backdrop.ready via :has()
     so it engages ONLY when a wallpaper is actually shown (a flat dark/light home ⇒ backdrop never turns ready
     ⇒ the chat keeps its solid default, still matching home). Scoped to the default look (html:not([data-skin]))
     so the opt-in skins / theatre keep their own immersive treatment untouched. -->
